     <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-09-02 -->
	 
	 Launching Naked Conversations
	 </font>
     </h2>
    

	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div><div align="center"><table id="table3" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" border="0"><tbody><tr><td><img height="90" src="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/viaggio/2006/02/F060221a.jpg" width="141" align="middle" border="0" /><img height="90" src="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/viaggio/2006/02/F060220a.jpg" width="193" align="middle" border="0" /><img height="90" src="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/viaggio/2006/02/F060223a.jpg" width="219" align="middle" border="0" /><img height="90" src="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/viaggio/2006/02/F060225a.jpg" width="139" align="middle" border="0" /></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>&nbsp; <table width="100%" align="center" border="0"><tbody><tr><td valign="top" align="middle" width="50%"><table id="table1" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellpadding="0" width="100%" border="0"><tbody><tr><td valign="top"><a href="http://seems2shel.typepad.com/itseemstome/" target="_top"><img height="252" alt="Shel Israel flew up to the party with wife Paula" hspace="0" src="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/viaggio/2006/02/F060205a.jpg" width="216" align="right" border="0" /></a><a href="http://scobleizer.wordpress.com/" target="_top"><img height="252" alt="Robert Scoble autographing Naked Conversations at the launch party" hspace="0" src="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/viaggio/2006/02/F060203a.jpg" width="218" align="right" border="0" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></td><td valign="top" align="left"><div style="FLOAT: right; WIDTH: 107px; HEIGHT: 185px"><table id="table2" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellpadding="0" width="67%" align="right" border="0"><caption valign="bottom" align="bottom"><small><a href="http://search.barnesandnoble.com/booksearch/isbnInquiry.asp?userid=t82xdYkA2N&amp;isbn=047174719X&amp;itm=1" target="_top">Barnes &amp; Noble</a><br /><a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/047174719X/nakedconversa-20?creative=327641&amp;camp=14573&amp;link_code=as1" target="_top">Amazon.com</a></small></caption><tbody><tr><td><a href="http://www.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-047174719X.html" target="_top"><img height="150" alt="Naked Conversations: How Blogs Are Changing the Way Businesses Talk with Customers, by Robert Scoble and Shel Israel" src="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/viaggio/2006/xx/F06xx01.jpg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p><b><a href="http://orcmid.com/viaggio/2004/11/V041101f.htm">2006-01-21: The Naked Conversations Launch Party</a></b>.&nbsp; To celebrate the publication of <i>Naked Conversations</i>, a launch party was held in Medina, Washington, an interesting community along the shores of Lake Washington, convenient to Redmond (the East Side) and Seattle (the West Side).</p><p>This represented a major culmination of <a href="http://spaces.msn.com/theredcouch/Blog/cns!1pu14osYRd1qo-cP37HiEsow!105.entry" target="_top">the journey</a> that Robert Scoble and co-author Shel Israel began during the U.S. Thanksgiving Weekend of November, 2004.<small><br />&nbsp;&nbsp; </small></p></td></tr></tbody></table></p><p><font size="2">It was thrilling to watch the book unfold on the </font><a href="http://nakedconversations.com/" target="_top"><font size="2">Naked Conversations</font></a><font size="2"> (née </font><a href="http://redcouch.typepad.com/" target="_top"><font size="2">Red Couch</font></a><font size="2">) blog site.&nbsp; Part of the reward for me was being able to observe how the authors </font><a href="http://orcmid.com/blog/2004/12/swept-along-israel-outed-by-scoble.asp" target="_top"><font size="2">developed and expanded their collaboration</font></a><font size="2"> over time, starting with </font><a href="http://redcouch.typepad.com/weblog/2005/11/happy_anniversa_1.html" target="_top"><font size="2">Scoble's brash initiation</font></a><font size="2">.&nbsp; The book points out that the interviews on the blog are sometimes lengthier than those retained in the book.</font></p><p>&nbsp; <table width="100%" align="center" border="0"><tbody><tr><td align="middle" colspan="2"><img height="101" src="http://compagno/orcmid/viaggio/2006/03/F060303a.jpg" width="180" border="0" /><a name="Magic"><img height="102" alt="Steve Broback wows 'em with hilarious rope tricks and magic" hspace="0" src="http://compagno/orcmid/viaggio/2006/03/F060302a.jpg" width="183" border="0" /></a><img height="102" hspace="0" src="http://compagno/orcmid/viaggio/2006/03/F060301A.jpg" width="365" border="0" /></td></tr></tbody></table></p><p><font size="2">Update 2006-02-13: Attempted correction to tagging.</font></p><p align="center"><font size="2"><strong><font color="#800080">{tag: <a style="COLOR: #800080" href="http://technorati.com/tag/naked_conversations" rel="tag">Naked Conversations</a> <a style="COLOR: #800080" href="http://technorati.com/tag/orcmid" rel="tag">orcmid</a>}</font></strong></font></p><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom: 0.25em;"></div>
    </p>
